    "name": "Mesh convergence study — non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw FEA model to quantify discretization error in predicted construct stiffness and yield force. Four mesh densities (coarse, medium, fine, extra-fine) were evaluated; Richardson extrapolation was applied to estimate the grid convergence index (GCI). Results indicated monotonic convergence with a GCI below 2.1% for construct stiffness and 3.4% for yield force at the fine mesh density adopted for production runs. This activity was documented in the FEA verification report and referenced in the model credibility summary.",
    "activityType": "MeshConvergenceStudy",
